  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Video-based methods using GANs (Chen et al. 2019; Liang et al. 2017; Liu et al. 2021), transformers (Wang et al. 2021a; Selva et al. 2023) and stable diffusion (Chai et al. 2023; Karras et al. 2023; Ceylan et al. 2023) present a number of underlying challenges, including issues with temporal consistency and a lack of suitable quality assessment metrics.",
    "Furthermore, current methods rarely consider camera-based tasks, such as the optimal camera pose or trajectory for generating a video.",
    "Considering the current pace of research, we believe it won't be long before this is possible.",
    "In conclusion, generative AI is a powerful tool, likely to offer numerous solutions to production challenges moving forward.",
    "However in parallel, researchers must also address ethical issues; for example, relating to the release of code and/or pre-trained models."
  ],
